                Unlike white gold, it lacks a rhodium coating and resists tarnish due to its corrosion-free nature. Renowned for its malleability and hypoallergenic properties, it’s ideal for sensitive skin. Thirty times rarer than gold, platinum is a dazzling, long-lasting choice for jewelry..To be labeled as platinum, a piece must contain at least 90% purity and is often alloyed with metals like iridium or palladium for added strength.
              </span>
